feeGroupCustomerEmptyInfo: If the customer does not belong to any fee group, the system will charge that customer at 100% (with no fee reduction).
parentFeeGroupIdInfo: Linked Fee Group determines after which fee group rate the fee group will be calculated. It is not required. Example: The Customers group is at a rate of %80. We give a rate of %50 to the Personnel group that we will add and link it with the Customers group. In case we do not link it, the 50 TRY fee will be calculated only with %50 rate and the fee will be reflected as 25 TRY. But if we connect the Customers group, 50 TRY is first multiplied by %80 and then multiplied by %50. As a result, a fee of 20 TRY comes out.
